What she didn’t find was a path toward affordable housing.
In tandem, the city’s comprehensive “2040 plan” calls for new protections for renters, new demands on developers, and other moves to preserve and expand a now-thin supply of affordable housing.
Yet beneath it all, the question remains: Can any city really ease the affordable housing crunch?
Some residents, while saying they share the goal of affordable housing, don’t want to see the city zoned for greater density in such a broad-brush way.
“We need to really protect the affordable housing that we have,” she says in an interview later.